{"lemma":"سَمْتِ","slug":"سَمْتِ","root":"س.م.ت","root_slug":"س-م-ت","root_link":"/words/roots/س-م-ت","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":4,"pos_tags":["noun","verb"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":6},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n20623","n20627"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%B3%D9%8E%D9%85%D9%92%D8%AA%D9%90"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"road, way"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"mode or manner of conduct, modus vivendi","examples":[{"text":"وهذا لعمري من فضائل الشرط الإنساني عندما يتحرر من أنانية التمركز الذاتي. وليس مايكل بورتيلو نفسه ببعيد عن هذا السمت الإنساني.","english":"And this is a human requirement for my life of virtues, when one is freed of self-centered egoism. And Michael Portillo is himself not far from this mode of human conduct."}]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"gravity, staidness, steadiness, sedateness, calmness"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"region or quarter towards which the course is directed"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"compass direction"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"azimuth"}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"From Aramaic סֵימִטָא (sēmiṭā) from Latin sēmĭta, but later reanalysed as deriving from an Arabic root س م ت (s m t) which contains only denominal verbs however."},"ipa":null,"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n20623","headword_ar":"سَمْتٌ","root":"smt","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"[as an inf. n.] is"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"syn. with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qaSodN","text_ar":"قَصْدٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[in an intrans. sense], (S, * Msb,) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"hudFY","text_ar":"هُدًى"},{"kind":"text","text":"[in the sense of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ra$aAdN","text_ar":"رَشَادٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"], and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AisotiqaAmapN","text_ar":"اِسْتِقَامَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (Msb:) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Husonu naHowK","text_ar":"حُسْنُ نَحْوٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (M, K:) you say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"samata","text_ar":"سَمَتَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, M, K,) and"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K,) or in this case the former only, (TA,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"samotN","text_ar":"سَمْتٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (M, TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He pursued a right course;"},{"kind":"text","text":"syn."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qaSada","text_ar":"قَصَدَ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (S, TA:) or (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he followed a good direction"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, K, * TA *)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in the way of religion"},{"kind":"text","text":"[&c.]. (TA.) Accord. to Khálid Ibn- Dabbeh, it signifies (assumed tropical:)  The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"following the truth and the right way"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"direction, and being a good neighbour, and doing little harm."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) [But more commonly, or primarily, it relates to the course that one pursues in journeying.] An Arab of the desert, of [the tribe of] Keys, says,"},{"kind":"quote","text":"sawofa tajuwbiyna bigayori naEoti\n                      \n                     \n                        taEas~ufFA A^awo h`ka*aA biAls~amoti"},{"kind":"text","text":"i. e. ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Thou shalt traverse"},{"kind":"text","text":"(addressing a woman), or, more probably,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"ye shall traverse"},{"kind":"text","text":"(addressing camels or other beasts), a land"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"without a description"},{"kind":"text","text":"],"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"journeying without any sign of the way and without any track"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"for guidance"},{"kind":"text","text":"], such being the meaning of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tEs~fA","text_ar":"تعسّفا"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"or thus, pursuing a right course,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Als~amotu","text_ar":"السَّمْتُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"meaning"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlqaSodu","text_ar":"القَصْدُ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.) Accord. to Sh,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Als~amotu","text_ar":"السَّمْتُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The seeking, searching,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"inquiring, for,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"after, the right way"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"direction."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) ―         -b2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Als~amotu","text_ar":"السَّمْتُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"also signifies"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qaSdu AlT~ariyqi","text_ar":"قَصدُ الطَّرِيقِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[i. e."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"samotu AlT~ariyqi","text_ar":"سَمْتُ الطَّرِيقِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The road's having a right,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"direct, tendency"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (M:) or ["},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"samotu Al$~aYo'i","text_ar":"سَمْتُ الشَّىْءِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"] signifies"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qaSodu Al$~aYo'i","text_ar":"قَصْدُ الشَّىْءِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The thing's having a right,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"direct, tendency"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (K.) [This last explanation has been misunderstood by the Turkish translator of the K; who has hence been led to assert that one says,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"samata Al$~aYo'a","text_ar":"سَمَتَ الشَّىْءَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"as well as"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"samata naHowahu","text_ar":"سَمَتَ نَحْوَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", meaning"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qaSadahu","text_ar":"قَصَدَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":": it is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tasam~atahu","text_ar":"تَسَمَّتَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"that (like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"samata naHowahu","text_ar":"سَمَتَ نَحْوَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":") signifies"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qaSadahu","text_ar":"قَصَدَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; not"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"samatahu","text_ar":"سَمَتَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"samata","text_ar":"سَمَتَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is always intrans.] ―         -b3-  Also"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The journeying"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, M, K)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"upon the road"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, K) ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"guided only"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"by opinion"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, M, K)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and conjecture:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S:) or, as some say,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the journeying by conjecture and opinion, not upon a"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"known"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"road."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) A poet says,"},{"kind":"quote","text":"↓ \n      layosa bihaA riyEN lisamoti Als~aAmiti"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"There is not,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"was not, in it, a road of any kind"},{"kind":"text","text":"(see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"riyEN","text_ar":"رِيعٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":")"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"for the journeying by opinion and conjecture of him who so journeys"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (S, TA.) ―         -b4-  And"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The pursuing a course,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"direction,"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of any kind,"},{"kind":"text","text":"] and [particularly] (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in religion and in worldly affairs."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) You say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"huwa yasomutu samotahu","text_ar":"هُوَ يَسْمُتُ سَمْتَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He pursues his"},{"kind":"text","text":"[another's]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"way,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"course, doing as he"},{"kind":"text","text":"[the latter]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"does."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) ["},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"samotahu","text_ar":"سَمْتَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is here an absolute (not an objective) complement of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yasomutu","text_ar":"يَسْمُتُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sayorahu","text_ar":"سَيْرَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"in the phrase"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"huwayasiyru sayorahu","text_ar":"هُوَيَسِيرُ سَيْرَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":". See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"samotN","text_ar":"سَمْتٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"below.] ―         -b5-  Also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"samata","text_ar":"سَمَتَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"samotN","text_ar":"سَمْتٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He"},{"kind":"text","text":"(a man)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"was,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"became, grave, staid, steady, sedate,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"calm."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb.) ―         -b6-  And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"samata lahumo","text_ar":"سَمَتَ لَهُمْ"},{"kind":"text","text":", aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", (Fr, K,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"samotN","text_ar":"سَمْتٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Fr, TA,) (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He prepared, arranged,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"disposed, for them, the mode,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"manner, of speech,"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of judging,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"forming an opinion,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Fr, K, TA,) and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of work,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"action."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Fr, TA.)"}],"source_refs":["Msb","M","K","S","TA","Fr"]},{"entry_id":"n20627","headword_ar":"سَمْتٌ","root":"smt","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"inf. n. of 1 [q. v.]. (M, TA.) ―         -b2-  Also"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A road,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"way;"},{"kind":"text","text":"syn."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"TariyqN","text_ar":"طَرِيقٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, M, A, Mgh, Msb, K,) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maHaj~apN","text_ar":"مَحَجَّةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Th, S,) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"naHowN","text_ar":"نَحْوٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (A:) [pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sumuwtN","text_ar":"سُمُوتٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":".] One says,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ailozamo h`*aA Als~amota","text_ar":"اِلْزَمْ هٰذَا السَّمْتَ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Keep thou to this road,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"way."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) ―         -b3-  And [hence,] (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The way,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"course, that one pursues in his religion and his worldly affairs:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a way, mode,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"manner, of acting"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"conduct"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the like:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, TA:) (tropical:)  the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"mode,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"manner,"},{"kind":"text","text":"[of life,] syn."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"hayoy^ap","text_ar":"هَيْيَة"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, A, Mgh, Msb, K, TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of good people,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, A, Mgh, K, TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in respect of religion,"},{"kind":"text","text":"not in"},{"kind":"page_break","n":1422},{"kind":"text","text":"respect of goodliness of person: (TA:) a metaphorical meaning, from the same word as signifying “ a road, ” or “ way. ” (Mgh.) One says,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_in~ahu laHasanu Als~amoti","text_ar":"اـِنَّهُ لَحَسَنُ السَّمْتِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Verily he is good in respect of the way,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"course, that he pursues in his religion and his worldly affairs:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"huwaHasanu","text_ar":"هُوَحَسَنُ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Als~amoti","text_ar":"السَّمْتِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"means (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he is good in his"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"hayoy^ap","text_ar":"هَيْيَة"},{"kind":"text","text":"[i. e., as here used,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"mode,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"manner, of life"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (Msb.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maA A^aHosana samotahu","text_ar":"مَا اَحْسَنَ سَمْتَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"How good is his way, mode,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"manner, of acting"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"conduct"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the like!"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, A, * Mgh, * TA.) ―         -b4-  [Hence,] (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Gravity, staidness, steadiness, sedateness,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"calmness."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb.) ―         -b5-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Als~amotu","text_ar":"السَّمْتُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"also signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The region,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"quarter, to which,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"towards which, the course,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"aim, is directed."},{"kind":"text","text":"(M.) ―         -b6-  [And hence,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The bearing,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"direction, of an object by the compass."},{"kind":"text","text":"And more particularly,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The azimuth."},{"kind":"text","text":"―         -b7-  And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"samotu Alr~aA^osi","text_ar":"سَمْتُ الرَّاْسِ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The zenith;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"vertical point in the heavens."},{"kind":"text","text":"(“ Zenit ” appears to have been, as Golius observes, a mistranscription for “ zemt, ” or “ semt. ”) ―         -b8-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"samotu Al$~amosi","text_ar":"سَمْتُ الشَّمْسِ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The path of the sun; the ecliptic:"},{"kind":"text","text":"from"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"samotN","text_ar":"سَمْتٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifying “ a road, ” or “ way. ” ―         -b9-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"samotu AlAiEotidaAli","text_ar":"سَمْتُ الاِعْتِدَالِ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The equinoctial colure."},{"kind":"text","text":"And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"samotu AlAinoqilaAbi","text_ar":"سَمْتُ الاِنْقِلَابِ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The solstitial colure."},{"kind":"text","text":"]"}],"source_refs":["S","M","A","Mgh","Msb","K","Th","TA"]}]},"classical_definitions":null}